#: ../../../topics/api.rst:5
msgid "Core API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:9
msgid ""
"This section documents the Scrapy core API, and it's intended for developers "
"of extensions and middlewares."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:15
msgid "Crawler API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:17
msgid ""
"The main entry point to Scrapy API is the :class:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler` "
"object, passed to extensions through the ``from_crawler`` class method. This "
"object provides access to all Scrapy core components, and it's the only way "
"for extensions to access them and hook their functionality into Scrapy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:25
msgid ""
"The Extension Manager is responsible for loading and keeping track of "
"installed extensions and it's configured through the :setting:`EXTENSIONS` "
"setting which contains a dictionary of all available extensions and their "
"order similar to how you :ref:`configure the downloader middlewares <topics-"
"downloader-middleware-setting>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:33
msgid ""
"The Crawler object must be instantiated with a :class:`scrapy.settings."
"Settings` object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:38
msgid "The settings manager of this crawler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:40
msgid ""
"This is used by extensions & middlewares to access the Scrapy settings of "
"this crawler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:43
msgid "For an introduction on Scrapy settings see :ref:`topics-settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:45
msgid "For the API see :class:`~scrapy.settings.Settings` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:49
msgid "The signals manager of this crawler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:51
msgid ""
"This is used by extensions & middlewares to hook themselves into Scrapy "
"functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:54
msgid "For an introduction on signals see :ref:`topics-signals`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:56
msgid "For the API see :class:`~scrapy.signalmanager.SignalManager` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:60
msgid "The stats collector of this crawler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:62
msgid ""
"This is used from extensions & middlewares to record stats of their "
"behaviour, or access stats collected by other extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:65
msgid "For an introduction on stats collection see :ref:`topics-stats`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:67
msgid "For the API see :class:`~scrapy.statscol.StatsCollector` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:71
msgid "The extension manager that keeps track of enabled extensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:73 ../../../topics/api.rst:83
msgid "Most extensions won't need to access this attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:75
msgid ""
"For an introduction on extensions and a list of available extensions on "
"Scrapy see :ref:`topics-extensions`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:80
msgid ""
"The spider manager which takes care of loading and instantiating spiders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:87
msgid ""
"The execution engine, which coordinates the core crawling logic between the "
"scheduler, downloader and spiders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:90
msgid ""
"Some extension may want to access the Scrapy engine, to modify inspect or "
"modify the downloader and scheduler behaviour, although this is an advanced "
"use and this API is not yet stable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:96
msgid "Configure the crawler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:98
msgid ""
"This loads extensions, middlewares and spiders, leaving the crawler ready to "
"be started. It also configures the execution engine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:103
msgid ""
"Start the crawler. This calls :meth:`configure` if it hasn't been called "
"yet. Returns a deferred that is fired when the crawl is finished."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:109
msgid "Settings API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:116
msgid ""
"Dictionary that sets the key name and priority level of the default settings "
"priorities used in Scrapy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:119
msgid ""
"Each item defines a settings entry point, giving it a code name for "
"identification and an integer priority. Greater priorities take more "
"precedence over lesser ones when setting and retrieving values in the :class:"
"`~scrapy.settings.Settings` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:128
msgid ""
"SETTINGS_PRIORITIES = {\n"
"    'default': 0,\n"
"    'command': 10,\n"
"    'project': 20,\n"
"    'cmdline': 40,\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:135
msgid ""
"For a detailed explanation on each settings sources, see: :ref:`topics-"
"settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:140
msgid ""
"This object stores Scrapy settings for the configuration of internal "
"components, and can be used for any further customization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:143
msgid ""
"After instantiation of this class, the new object will have the global "
"default settings described on :ref:`topics-settings-ref` already populated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:147
msgid ""
"Additional values can be passed on initialization with the ``values`` "
"argument, and they would take the ``priority`` level.  If the latter "
"argument is a string, the priority name will be looked up in :attr:`~scrapy."
"settings.SETTINGS_PRIORITIES`. Otherwise, a expecific integer should be "
"provided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:153
msgid ""
"Once the object is created, new settings can be loaded or updated with the :"
"meth:`~scrapy.settings.Settings.set` method, and can be accessed with the "
"square bracket notation of dictionaries, or with the :meth:`~scrapy.settings."
"Settings.get` method of the instance and its value conversion variants.  "
"When requesting a stored key, the value with the highest priority will be "
"retrieved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:162
msgid "Store a key/value attribute with a given priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:164
msgid ""
"Settings should be populated *before* configuring the Crawler object "
"(through the :meth:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler.configure` method), otherwise "
"they won't have any effect."
msgstr ""

