msgid "the value to return if no setting is found"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:220
msgid ""
"Get a setting value as a boolean. For example, both ``1`` and ``'1'``, and "
"``True`` return ``True``, while ``0``, ``'0'``, ``False`` and ``None`` "
"return ``False````"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:224
msgid ""
"For example, settings populated through environment variables set to ``'0'`` "
"will return ``False`` when using this method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:235
msgid "Get a setting value as an int"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:245
msgid "Get a setting value as a float"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:255
msgid ""
"Get a setting value as a list. If the setting original type is a list it "
"will be returned verbatim. If it's a string it will be split by \",\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:258
msgid ""
"For example, settings populated through environment variables set to ``'one,"
"two'`` will return a list ['one', 'two'] when using this method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:270
msgid "Signals API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:279
msgid "Connect a receiver function to a signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:281
msgid ""
"The signal can be any object, although Scrapy comes with some predefined "
"signals that are documented in the :ref:`topics-signals` section."
msgstr ""

